eloping and highly playful genre of the novel. Indeed, García Santo-Tomás makes a strong case that the rise of the novel cannot be fully understood without taking into account its relationship to the scientific discoveries of the period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLiterature and sciencezSpainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSciencezSpainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSpanish fictionyClassical period, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBaroque.  aGalileo Galilei.  aSpain.  aliterature.  aoptics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022637646240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226465876423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226465876/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles